THE CENTRAL ELEGANT POINT (CEP) - THE ANCHOR
What Makes a Good CEP?
You've identified the key property: Universal mathematical elegance

Your list of CEPs:

Constants: e, π, φ (golden ratio), 1, 0, √2, √3
Sequences: Fibonacci, Catalan numbers, triangular numbers, primes
Structures: Perfect squares, perfect cubes, Pythagorean triples
Geometric: Circle (x² + y² = r²), area formulas (½bh), special angles (30°, 45°, 60°)
Identities: e^(iπ) + 1 = 0, sin²θ + cos²θ = 1, (a+b)² = a² + 2ab + b²
Why these work as CEPs:

✅ Universally recognized (students know these are "special")
✅ Inherently beautiful (surprising, simple, profound)
✅ Memorable (sticky in mind)
