7. THE TWO-STAGE PROCESS: MVC TO FORMALIZATION
7.1 The Separation of Thinking and Writing
The Advaitian Philosophy deliberately separates intuitive reasoning (Stage 1) from formal exposition (Stage 2). This reflects a deep pedagogical truth:

Thinking happens before writing. Intuition precedes formalization.

Traditional education conflates these stages, demanding rigor before understanding. The result: students manipulate symbols without grasping meaning.

The Advaitian separation:

Stage 1 (MVC): Pure thinking—conversational, open-ended, forgiving
Stage 2 (Formalization): Rigorous structure—ready for publication
This protects the intuitive phase from premature formalization.

7.2 Stage 1: The Minimum Viable Commentary (MVC)
Definition: The MVC is the "inner voice"—what runs through a student's mind in the first 60 seconds after seeing a problem.

What it IS:

Conversational capture of: seed intuition, brute trap, elegant pivot
NO equations, NO formalism, NO polish
The SOUL of the commentary—pure structural thinking
What it is NOT:

Mathematical rigor or complete proofs
All six framework sections
Polished prose ready for publication
The Three Meta-Questions (First Minute Protocol):

What stays constant? → Look for Invariance, Symmetry
What changes form? → Look for Translation, Substitution, Linearization
What filters solutions? → Look for Domain Constraints, Bounds, Existence
Example MVC (Polygon Problem):

"The seed here is to connect arithmetic progression with sum of internal angles of a polygon. The sum is the 'invariant' here. Smallest angle being 120° eliminates some options. This is also a bounds problem—what's the maximum number of sides after applying AP rules?

The elegance lies in right assumptions and elimination. The key invariant is the highest angle—must be < 180°. The key move is checking the AP against the 180° ceiling. That constraint prunes the search space in one shot.

So by connecting AP, polygon geometry, invariant, and logical substitution, the answer arrives.

The brute trap is mechanical substitution from n=3 onward without considering the mathematical logic above."

Validation criteria:

✅ Seed intuition present? (Can I identify the archetype?)
✅ Brute-force space recognizable? (Can I see the trap?)
✅ Elegant pivot present? (Can I identify the key insight?)
If YES to all three: "Your MVC is solid. Ready for Stage 2."

7.3 Stage 2: The Gold-Standard Commentary
Purpose: Transform the conversational MVC into a publication-ready, pedagogically rigorous six-point commentary.

Characteristics:

Rigorous: Mathematically precise, no hand-waving
Complete: All six sections fully developed
Structured: Follows the framework exactly
Polished: Ready for the book without further editing
Rich: Includes equations, alternative approaches, cross-domain connections
The Transformation:

MVC Element	Stage 2 Section	Transformation
Seed intuition	SEED	Crystallize into one-sentence archetype statement
Brute-force space	BRUTE PATH	Expand with concrete steps and equations
Elegant pivot	ELEGANT PIVOT	Formalize the insight, show the mathematics
(Implicit)	PITFALLS	Enumerate 3-5 named cognitive traps
(Implicit)	CONNECTIONS	Add primary applications + alternatives + cross-domain
(Implicit)	TAKEAWAY	Distill into one memorable principle
Stage 2 construction guidelines:

Write SEED first (identifies archetype explicitly)
Build BRUTE PATH with step-by-step equations
Formalize ELEGANT PIVOT (name the insight, show the math)
Enumerate PITFALLS (name each, explain why tempting)
Develop CONNECTIONS (three subsections: primary, alternative, cross-domain)
Craft TAKEAWAY (memorable, under 15 words, actionable)
7.4 The Workflow
For Each Problem:

